&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Software Engineer to join our growing engineering team. In this role, you will design, build, and operate scalable software platforms that support analytics and AI solutions. You will contribute to system architecture, cloud deployments, and modern containerized environments, while collaborating with multidisciplinary teams across regions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;What This Involves:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain high-quality software solutions using Python.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the design and evolution of scalable and maintainable software architectures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deploy, operate, and monitor applications in cloud environments (AWS, Azure, or GCP).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage containerized applications using Docker and Kubernetes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the development and deployment of AI and analytics solutions, working closely with data scientists and data engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with cross-functional and client-facing teams to deliver end-to-end solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in technical discussions, architectural and code reviews, and continuous improvement initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to internal and client-mandated data protection and compliance policies, ensuring all handling, storage, and sharing of data meets required security and privacy standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;Requirements:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science or related fields.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong Python knowledge with 5+ years of experience building production-grade software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong SQL skills, including writing complex queries, joins, and aggregations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience operating and deploying solutions in cloud environments (any major cloud provider).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practical knowledge of container technologies and architectures, including Docker and Kubernetes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic understanding of AI solution components and technologies, such as LLMs, vector databases, APIs/protocols, and supporting infrastructure.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in systems design, particularly in cloud-native or distributed environments is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to overlap with Pacific Time business hours for a minimum of 3 hours per day.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why You Will Love It Here:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work on real-world AI and advanced analytics solutions with measurable business impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with a global team of engineers and data scientists.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to diverse industries, modern cloud platforms, and cutting-edge AI technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A collaborative culture that values real outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High ownership, zero micromanagement&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rapid learning opportunities and diverse challenges&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible work hours, remote-friendly setup&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flat organisational hierarchy with high visibility and accessibility to our leaders&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lynx Analytics is an AI-native consulting firm focused on solving complex challenges for global life sciences organizations. We work with leading pharma, biotech, and medtech organisations to design and deliver high-impact solutions — from AI-driven commercial analytics to pharmacovigilance and patient insights. Our work is hands-on, deeply technical, and built around real client outcomes&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our clients include some of the world’s largest pharmaceutical companies — spanning oncology, commercial analytics, and beyond. We are a lean, expert team and we are growing. This is an early, foundational hire — and the opportunity to shape how we go to market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are hiring a VP of Sales to build and lead our commercial function from the ground up. This is a hands-on leadership role at a real inflection point: Lynx has strong delivery capability, a growing reputation, and a clear set of service offerings — and we are ready to scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work directly with the CEO and leadership team to turn that foundation into a consistent, scalable revenue engine. You will define how we sell, what we lead with, and where we focus. Critically, you will not just build the playbook — you will execute it. Early on, that means personally driving and closing key deals while putting the systems and structure in place to grow the team over time.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are energised by building something from scratch — and by winning business that genuinely matters — this is that role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What This Involves:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and deliver on revenue targets across target markets and accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personally lead and close strategic engagements, particularly in the early phase&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define Lynx’s go-to-market: positioning, service packaging, pricing, and messaging&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the full sales motion — from pipeline generation and qualification through to deal close and account expansion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish practical, lightweight systems for pipeline visibility, forecasting, and account planning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and steward senior relationships across pharma, biotech, and medtech clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recruit, onboard, and grow the commercial team as the business scales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent Lynx in senior client settings, industry conferences, and key forums&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who We&#39;re Looking For:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have a track record of winning and growing consulting or solutions-based business in life sciences — and you know how to operate in environments where the deals are complex, the buyers are senior, and the relationship matters as much as the proposal.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10–15+ years in commercial roles, with meaningful experience building or scaling a sales or business development function&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep credibility in life sciences — whether from the commercial, data, digital, or R&amp;amp;D side&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A background in selling analytics, AI, or professional services engagements — where the value is in expertise and outcomes, not just the product&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuine builder’s mindset: energised by ambiguity, and skilled at creating structure without over-engineering it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong operator who can translate vision into consistent day-to-day execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive presence and comfort engaging VP and C-suite stakeholders — as a peer, not just a vendor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Global exposure across the US, Europe, or Asia is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Motivated by long-term value creation — and the equity upside that comes with building something significant&lt;
